<TITLE> NBR sues Mosaddek Ali Falu for dodging tax </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 27 (bdnews24.com)The National Board of Revenue filed a tax-dodge case against former BNP lawmaker Mosaddek Ali Falu on Tuesday. NBR deputy tax commissioner Nurul Amin filed the case with the Dhaka Metropolitan Sessions Judge's Court. Judge Azizul Hoque accepted the case and fixed June 2 for a hearing. The judge also ordered that Falu be produced in court on the day. The case alleged that Falu had dodged more than Tk 11.21 crore in income tax from 1996 to 2006. Falu was arrested on Feb 3 last year. bdnew
